:11pt">the bus is vital to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">access employment, education</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, training and healthcare.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Where communities do not have access to public transportation social mobility is restricted as there are only more expensive private forms of transportation. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We then seek to address the specific que</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">stions posed by the Committee</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. In particular we put forward recommendations which we hope might improve community transport and demand responsive transport, we hope the Government might explore some of these suggestions. Finally we seek to answer the quest</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ion on affordability, where we suggest ways the Government might make passenger transport more affordable for those in isolated communities.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We hope that our evidence is of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">use</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to the Committee.  We would of course be delighted to provide further explanat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ion or additional information if that would be of use.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">About Greener Journeys</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is a campaign to encourage fewer car journeys and more trips by bus and coach. We aim to increase the value of bus and coach travel in stimulating economic gro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">wth, reducing congestion and CO2 emissions and enabling access to jobs, retail, leisure and vital services.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys is a coalition of Britain’s leading bus companies and other supporters including</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Transport for London, Campaign for Better Transpo</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rt, the RAC Foundation, Confederation for Passenger Transport (CPT), and the Passenger Transport Executive Group (pteg).</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Its primary funders are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">bus companies Arriva, FirstGroup, Go-Ahead, and Stagecoach.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Bus transportation is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">vital for communities</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">For </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">people in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">communities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are isolated</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> be it geographically or socially</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a lack of access to affordable passenger transport </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">inhibits</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> access to employment, education</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> training, and healthcare. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Passenger </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">transport provision plays a key role in promoting social mobility, and for many the bus is the only available form. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Accessing employmen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">t</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">One in ten</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> bus commuters would be forced to look for another job or give up work altogether if they could no longer commute by bus</span><a name="_ednref1"></a><a href="#_edn1">[i]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> quarter</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> have turned down a job because it was not located on a bus route (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">including </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">one in ten</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> during</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the last 12 months)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Accessi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ng education and training</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">More than 50% students are frequent bus users. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">If they could no longer travel by bus to their education or training, 12% would miss sessions, and 6% would have to look for different (less suitable) course. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">30% of those most depe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ndent on bus services to access their education and training courses live in the top 10% of most deprived areas.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6% </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">16-24 year olds turn down training or education because of transport problems</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Accessing healthcare</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">31% of people without a car have difficulty travelling to their local hospital. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">44% of people without a car have difficulty getting to their doctor.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Questions</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">How do Government and local authorities identify demand for passenger transport in isolated co</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">mmunities (including rural and urban areas and island communities)? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Not applicable</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people, young people) taken into account in determining the provision</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> of public transport to isolated communities?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Not applicable</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">What are the main challenges associated with providing better a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">nd more consistent bus and rail </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">services to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Isolated </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rural </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">communities have low density demand for transport as they are sparsely populated</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rban isolated communities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">often </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lack the economic resource to pay for private transport or demand responsive public transport such as private hire vehicles. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">geographicall</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">y isolated </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(though not necessarily poorer) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">communities, the distance necessary to travel renders swift public and private travel prohibitively expensive.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in isolated communiti</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">es? How could Community Transport be improved?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys is not able to comment on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">how</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> community transport </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">functions </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">but</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">we welcome </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the contribution that</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">it </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">makes</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to driving down CO2 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">emissions </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and making travel accessible to isolated communities.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys has worked with</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the charity Pure Innovations</span><a name="_ednref2"></a><a href="#_edn2">[ii]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> a national non-profit charity which seeks to support the disabled and disadvantaged to be independent,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to enable them to make the most of their capacity and potential.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  This work is part of a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">wider programme exploring a variety of locally developed schemes to encourage passengers to make the switch from car to bus.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> charity sought to enable young people to travel </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">independently </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">using public transport. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ommunity transport is useful,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">it </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">reinforces and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">separation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> between the user and the rest of the community.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Pure Innovations scheme facilitated </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">community integration</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">improving independence and confidence and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">helping young peopl</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to take advantage of opportunities in work and recreatio</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">n.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This was only a small local pilot in Stockport</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> however the results were extremely positive. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">More detail is available in Greener Journeys’ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Behaviour Change Lab</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> report</span><a name="_ednref3"></a><a href="#_edn3">[iii]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">recommends that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the Government explore</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> similar schemes promoting independence for disadvantaged people and those with a disability. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">There</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> a number of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">inn</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ovative </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">demand-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">responsive transport</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> schemes.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">CallConnect ser</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">vice</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, backed by Lincolnshire County Council </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has drawn prais</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e. For example users in a recent survey rated the service between 98-99% satisfaction on all counts.</span><a name="_ednref4"></a><a href="#_edn4">[iv]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The award-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">winning</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Call</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Connect</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">service </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has shown</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">how </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">local</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> authorities can provide</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> rural transportation services.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Private schemes can also be effective</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  In</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Turkey</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> share taxis known locally as</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">dolmuş</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> offer passengers travel along set routes only when a sufficient number of passengers </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have boarded. The scheme is regulated by the Turkish Government </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> an established and popular mode of transport. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Government should explore the potential for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">innovative schemes such as these to meet the challenge</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of rural transportation.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">isolated communities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">should not be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services. As much as possible, public transport should be available and only where that is not viable should they be expected to rely on demand-responsive pr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ivate transport.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Low density of demand in isolated communities leads to uncompetitive transport markets. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">It is widely accepted that uncompetitive transport </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">market</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> result in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lower investment</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in turn </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">results in poor quality of infrastructure and diversity of vehicle types, limiting the options for isolated communities.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">There </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">also can be </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a lack of understanding from government and government agencies of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the potential benefits </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">increasing the efficiency with which transport services are provided. This affects financial support for passenger transport, particularly at a time when tra</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nsport budgets are under threat from wider budget cuts</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">How can these s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ervices be made more affordable?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Service affordability is critically important, especially in the current economic climate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Currently responsibility for transport provision </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rests </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">at the local council level, with transport authorities, and with the Departm</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ent for Transport. This leads to staf</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fing and management replication.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Better coordinated </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">transport budget management</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is needed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to ensure proper efficiency</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Ultimately though affordability </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">best calculated as value for money. This</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> calculation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> should be b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ased </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">upon investment in transport set against the benefits returned by this investment.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">To make these services more affordable for users</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Government </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ould </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">explore </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">how </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the elderly person bus pass </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">scheme </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">might be replicated</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for different </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">types of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">users </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in need of transportation support. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">For example </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">during January 2013, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ran </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the innovative national campaign ‘Bus for Jobs’ where more than 800,000 unemployed job seekers were offered free bus travel.</span><a name="_ednref5"></a><a href="#_edn5">[v]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Greener Journeys welcomed the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Government’s recent announcement</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of measures</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> on the Bus Service Operators Grant</span><a name="_ednref6"></a><a href="#_edn6">[vi]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">aim to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ensure that this country’s essential bus services continue to serve the people that need them across the country</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he Government </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">should </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">continue to support bus </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">se</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">rvices </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in this way.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt">Page </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">4</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="